VK_WARNING: Validation Performance Warning: [ UNASSIGNED-BestPractices-vkCreateRenderPass-image-requires-memory ] Object 0: handle = 0x62800001c100, type = VK_OBJECT_TYPE_DEVICE; | MessageID = 0x4003982 | Attachment 2 in the VkRenderPass is a multisampled image with 4 samples, but it uses loadOp/storeOp which requires accessing data from memory. Multisampled images should always be loadOp = CLEAR or DONT_CARE, storeOp = DONT_CARE. This allows the implementation to use lazily allocated memory effectively. (performance)


That's a consequence of the skybox fixes. To hide geometry errors in levels and the way the skybox coordinates are calculated, creating geometry that's not watertight, I made the game load the contents of the previous frame before drawing the next one on it, visually masking many errors in the same way the OpenGL renderer does. These changes mean the color attachment (single sample or multisample) has to be loaded when the render pass starts and always stored after drawing, hence the warning. Nothing to worry about, IMHO.

