Changes contains only changes for non color light.
Color lighting can be wrong as for me and requires additional changes, look to
	if ((light_masked[0] | light_masked[1] | light_masked[2]) <= vid_lightthreshold)
	{
		// FIXME: color conversion should be applied and based on vid_colormap
		return pix;
	}

here should be something like return vid_colormap[pix + min(light[0], light[1], light[2])], because white color before vid_lightthreshold has no differences in RGB value, I suppose there should some applying color light and texture should be brighter and more white for color pixels different to white.
Light in this place is not brightness of pixel but destination from light source. So (0,0,0) is bright pixel, (0xff00, 0xff00, 0xff00) is dark pixel.
